### Artifact 2: AU-12 Moderate Finding Notification

*Subject: Moderate Security Finding — AU-12 Audit Logging / AO Notification Required*

[AO name],

Per Authorization Condition 3, I am notifying you of a Moderate severity finding identified during the ISSO's semi-annual self-assessment on [date].

**Finding:** Denied access events are not being captured in the OpenMRS audit log. When a user attempts to access a patient record outside their role permissions, the access is correctly blocked by the access control enforcement — but the denied attempt is not generating an audit log entry. Successful access, successful authentication, and record modifications are all logged correctly.

**Why this matters:** This reduces our ability to detect two scenarios: (1) systematic credential probing before an unauthorized access event (RS-001), and (2) insider probing of records just outside role scope (RS-005). Both scenarios generate denied access attempts that we currently cannot see in the audit log.

**What is not affected:** Access controls are functioning — denied access attempts are being correctly blocked. Encryption, backup, and network security controls are unaffected. This is a detection gap, not an access control failure.

**Remediation plan:** Investigating OpenMRS audit log module configuration; if a configuration fix is available, implementation and verification will be completed by [date]. If an application limitation, a compensating CloudWatch metric filter will be implemented. Target completion: [date].

**Compensating controls during remediation:** GuardDuty behavioral anomaly detection and quarterly access reviews remain active.

I will provide a status update at the 45-day check-in. This finding will be entered as a new Moderate POA&M item and tracked per the standard management process.

[ISSO name]

