### Artifact 3: Phishing Simulation Program Approval Request

*To: Health IT Manager*
*Subject: Phishing Simulation Program — 15 Minutes of Your Time for Q2 Launch*

[Name],

I want to launch our quarterly phishing simulation program in Q2. I need approximately 15 minutes of your time — and I want to be upfront about why this matters now more than it did at authorization.

The Q1 HC3 threat intelligence briefing identified phishing campaigns specifically targeting healthcare organizations matching our profile as the primary vector for both credential theft and ransomware. Our training completion is 100%. We have no data on whether our staff would actually recognize a targeted phishing email.

The program I am proposing: once per quarter, I send a simulated phishing email to all staff. Users who click are redirected to a brief educational page showing the red flags they missed. You would send one advance message to staff explaining what phishing simulations are and that results are used for learning, not discipline. I report aggregate click rates to you — not individual names.

My setup time: approximately 4 hours to configure GoPhish (self-hosted, no cost). Your time: drafting the advance staff notice with me — I can have a draft ready before we meet.

Given what the HC3 briefing said about our threat profile, I am not comfortable telling the AO our human layer is prepared without any evidence that it is. This program is how we get that evidence.

Can we find 20 minutes this week or next to draft the staff notice together?

[ISSO name]

